def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    """Returns priority with which we want to add item to each bin.

    Args:
        item: Size of item to be added to the bin.
        bins: Array of capacities for each bin.

    Return:
        Array of same size as bins with priority score of each bin.
    """
    """More complex version of priority function."""
    
    def calculate_priority(item: float, bin_capacity: float) -> float:
        if item <= bin_capacity:  # If item can fit in the bin
            return 1 + item / bin_capacity  # Priority is 1 + ratio of item to bin capacity
        else:
            return 1 - (item - bin_capacity) / item  # Priority is 1 minus ratio of remaining item to total item
    
    item_arr = np.full_like(bins, item)  # Create an array of the same size as bins filled with item value
    remaining_space = bins - item_arr  # Calculate remaining space in each bin after adding item

    priorities = np.zeros_like(bins)  # Initialize array to store priorities

    for i in range(len(bins)):
        priorities[i] = calculate_priority(item, bins[i])  # Calculate priority for each bin
        
    return priorities
